Few factors to note - US has released 1mn barrels per day from strategic oil reserves for 6 months so thats 180mn barrels for the year. US Consumption of Motor Gasoline is about 8.5-9.2 mn barrels per day. US has about 500mn barrels in reserves, so there is still some more room for reserve releases and this being an election year, there is a possibility that those reserves will be utilized if the prices increase further. On the other hand oil consumption probably will increase near July from current levels (roughly by 5% based on looking at consumption pattern in the first 10 days of July over 2014-19, which i am assuming is the normalized consumption). https://www.cnbc.com/2022/03/31/us-to-release-1-million-barrels-of-oil-per-day-from-reserves-to-help-cut-gas-prices.html https://www.eia.gov/dnav/pet/hist/LeafHandler.ashx?n=PET&s=wgfupus2&f=W
